{"title_page": "David Cameron (footballer, born 1936)", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2017}}\n{{Use British English|date=March 2017}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n|name        = David Cameron\n|image       = \n|caption     = \n|fullname    = David Cameron<ref name=Hugman>{{Hugman|2978|accessdate=30 November 2017}}</ref>\n|birth_date  = {{birth date|df=y|1936|3|10}}<ref name=Hugman/>\n|birth_place = [[Glasgow]], Scotland\n|death_date  = {{death date and age|df=y|2006|6|27|1936|3|10}}<ref name=Hugman/>\n|death_place = Glasgow,<ref name=Hugman/> Scotland\n|height      = \n|position    = [[Inside forward]]\n|youthyears1 = \n|youthclubs1 = \n|years1      = \n|clubs1      = [[Rutherglen Glencairn F.C.|Rutherglen Glencairn]]\n|caps1       = \n|goals1      = \n|years2      = 1958\u20131959\n|clubs2      = [[Bradford City A.F.C.|Bradford City]]\n|caps2       = 7\n|goals2      = 2\n|years3      = \n|clubs3      = [[Ashfield F.C.|Ashfield]]\n|caps3       = \n|goals3      = \n|totalcaps   = \n|totalgoals  = \n}}\n'''David Cameron''' (10 March 1936 \u2013 27 June 2006) was a Scottish professional [[association football|footballer]] who played as an [[inside forward]].\n\n==Career==\nBorn in [[Glasgow]], Cameron played for [[Rutherglen Glencairn F.C.|Rutherglen Glencairn]], [[Bradford City A.F.C.|Bradford City]] and [[Ashfield F.C.|Ashfield]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.neilbrown.newcastlefans.com/player11/davidcameron.htm|title=David Cameron|website=Post War English & Scottish Football League A\u2013Z Player's Transfer Database|publisher=Neil Brown|accessdate=30 November 2017}}</ref><ref>Frost, p. 392</ref> For Bradford City, he made 7 appearances in [[the Football League]], scoring twice.<ref>Frost, p. 380</ref>\n\n==Sources==\n*{{cite book|last=Frost|first=Terry|title=Bradford City A Complete Record 1903-1988|publisher=Breedon Books Sport|year=1988|isbn=0-907969-38-0}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Cameron, David}}\n[[Category:1936 births]]\n[[