onference National]] club [[York City F.C.|York City]] on trial in July 2008,<ref>{{cite news\n |first       = Dave\n |last        = Flett\n |url         = http://www.yorkpress.co.uk/sport/yorkcityfc/news/3197703.Brown_stakes_claim_to_be_a_full_time_Minsterman/\n |title       = Brown stakes claim to be a full-time Minsterman\n |date        = 8 July 2008\n |accessdate  = 13 September 2012\n |newspaper   = The Press\n |location    = York\n |url-status     = dead\n |archiveurl  = https://archive.is/20130505111047/http://www.yorkpress.co.uk/sport/yorkcityfc/news/3197703.Brown_stakes_claim_to_be_a_full_time_Minsterman/\n |archivedate = 5 May 2013\n |df          = dmy-all\n}}</ref> scoring twice in a pre-season friendly game against [[Tadcaster Albion F.C.|Tadcaster Albion]], which York won 6\u20130.<ref name=\"tadcaster\">{{cite news\n |url        = http://www.yorkpress.co.uk/sport/yorkcityfc/news/3199036.City_boss_weighs_up_final_signing_to_bolster_squad/\n |archive-url = https://archive.is/20130505100528/http://www.yorkpress.co.uk/sport/yorkcityfc/news/3199036.City_boss_weighs_up_final_signing_to_bolster_squad/\n |url-status   = dead\n |archive-date = 5 May 2013\n |title      = City boss weighs up final signing to bolster squad\n |date       = 9 July 2008\n |accessdate = 13 September 2012\n |first      = Dave\n |last       = Flett\n |newspaper  = The Press\n |location   = York\n}}</ref> However, York manager [[Colin Walker (footballer born 1958)|Colin Walker]] said Brown and two other trialists were only making up the numbers and were unlikely to be signed permanently.<ref>{{cite news\n|url=http://newsimg.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/7499675.stm\n|title=York squad is complete \u2013 Walker\n|date=10 July 2008\n|accessdate=13 September 2012\n|publisher=BBC Sport}}</ref> Later the same month, he was given a trial at [[Northern Premier League Premier Division]] side [[Guiseley A.F.C.|Guiseley]], coming on as a second-half substitute in a 2\u20131 pre-season friendly victory over former side Bradford City.<ref>{{cite news\n|url=http://www.thetelegraphandargus.co.uk/sport/sportbcfc/sportbcfcmatch/3223044.Evans_gets_second_chance/\n|title=Evans gets second chance\n|date=22 July 2008\n|accessdate=13 September 2012\n|newspaper=Telegraph & Argus\n|location=Bradford\n|first=Simon\n|last=Parker}}</ref> After scoring 2 goals in another pre-season game against a Leeds United XI, he joined Guiseley on a permanent basis.<ref>{{cite news\n|url=http://www.thetelegraphandargus.co.uk/sport/football/footballguiseey/conference_north_2011_2012/news_articles/3563337.Guiseley_have_plenty_of_options_up_front_/\n|title=Guiseley have plenty of options up front\n|date=1 August 2008\n|accessdate=13 September 2012\n|newspaper=Telegraph & Argus\n|location=Bradford\n|first=Ian\n|last=Whiting}}</ref>\n\nIn January 2009, he joined [[Northern Premier League Division One North]] side [[F.C. Halifax Town|Halifax Town]] along with fellow Bradford City player [[Paul Evans (footballer born 1974)|Paul Evans]].<ref>{{cite news\n|url=http://www.halifaxcourier.co.uk/halifaxtown/Wakefield-v-FC-Halifax-Town.4930951.jp\n|title=Wakefield v FC Halifax Town: Two in, one out at the Shay\n|date=30 January 2009\n|accessdate=30 January 2009\n|newspaper=Halifax Courier}}</ref> Brown's debut was as a substitute one day after signing for Halifax, when he scored the final goal during a 4\u20131 victory against [[Wakefield F.C.|Wakefield]].<ref>{{cite news\n|url=http://www.halifaxcourier.co.uk/local/Wakefield-FC-v-FC-Halifax.4934164.jp\n|title=Wakefield FC v FC Halifax Town: Stott at the double\n|date=31 January 2009\n|accessdate=1 February 2009\n|newspaper=Halifax Courier}}</ref>\n\nBrown finished the season with Halifax, but in June 2009, he returned to [[Conference North]] side [[Eastwood Town F.C.|Eastwood Town]], where he had previously played on loan.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.eastwoodadvertiser.co.uk/sport/New-signings-to-bring-youth.5357130.jp |title=New signings to bring youth and experience |date=11 June 2009 |accessdate=28 January 2010 |first=Mark |last=Duffy |newspaper=Eastwood Advertiser}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{Soccerbase}}\n\n{{Hyde United F.C. squad}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Brown, David}}\n[[Category:1989 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Tadcaster]]\n[[Category:English footballers]]\n[[Category:Association football forwards]]\n[[Category:Leeds United F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Nottingham Forest F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Eastwood Town F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Bradford City A.F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Guiseley A.F.C. players]]\n[[Category:F.C. Halifax Town players]]\n[[Category:Bradford (Park Avenue) A.F.C. players]]\n[[Category:English Football League players]]\n[[Category:Tadcaster Albion A.F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Garforth Town A.F.C. players]]\n", "name_user": "GiantSnowman", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200etop:clean up", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/David_Brown_(footballer,_born_1989)"}
